The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 17: The rate of inflation hit a 13-month low at 4.22 per cent in the week ended June 4, although there are apprehensions that price levels would rise due to an imminent hike in fuel rates. Food items, some fuel and manufactured products became cheaper during the week. The point-to-point wholesale price index inflation was 5.20 per cent in the previous week. It was 6.70 per cent a year-ago.

 New Delhi, June 17: The cabinet committee on economic affairs will meet on Monday to decide on increasing the petrol and diesel prices, finance ministry sources said.

 Mumbai, June 17: General Motors (India) is planning to introduce two new models every year, including a small car in 2006. It is also considering a greenfield project.

 New Delhi, June 17: The Reserve Bank is sticking to its 7 per cent growth projection announced in the monetary policy despite the delay in monsoon, said RBI deputy governor Shyamala Gopinath.

 Mumbai, June 17: Motherson Sumi Systems Ltd has reached an agreement with German insolvency administrators to acquire a running plastics injection moulding company, G+S Kunststofftechnik, located near Stuttgart in Germany.




